{{define "content"}}<h2>Keys</h2>
<p>Most of the keys have a description in the TUI. Here are some info about the key that doesn't show up.</p>
<p class="highlight">Keys without description in tut</p>
<ul>
    <li>c = Compose a new toot</li>
    <li>jk = navigation up and down in feed</li>
    <li>hl = cycle through feeds without closing them as you do with q and ESC</li>
    <li>arrow keys = navigation. Same as jk and hl</li>
    <li>g or Home = go to top</li>
    <li>G or End = go to bottom</li>
    <li>? = show help</li>
    <li>q = go back and quit</li>
    <li>ESC = go back</li>
</ul>

<p class="highlight">Explanation of the non obvious keys when viewing a toot</p>

<ul>
    <li>V = view. In this mode you can scroll throught the text of the toot if it doesn't fit the screen</li>
    <li>O = open. Gives you a list of all URLs in the toot. Opens them in your default browser, if it's an user or tag they will be opened in tut.</li>
    <li>M = media. Opens the media with xdg-open.</li>
</ul>
{{end}}
